# Model Serving Workspace

This workspace contains multiple repositories for the RHOAI Model Serving stack.

## Directory Layout

```
model-serving/              # Workspace root
├── .cursor/                # Shared Cursor configuration
├── kserve/                 # kserve fork hierarchy (three-tier)
├── odh-model-controller/   # odh-model-controller fork hierarchy (two-tier)
└── ...
```

## Detecting the Active Repository

Determine which repo the user is working in from context:

| Signal | Repo |
|--------|------|
| Open file under `kserve/` | kserve |
| Open file under `odh-model-controller/` | odh-model-controller |
| User mentions "kserve", "isvc", "inferenceservice", "predictor", "transformer", "explainer" | kserve |
| User mentions "omc", "odh-model-controller", "routes", "authconfig", "authorino", "servicemesh" | odh-model-controller |
If ambiguous, ask: "Which repo? (kserve / odh-model-controller)"

See `repo-scope.mdc` for detailed responsibility boundaries between the two repos.

## Git Operations

Each subdirectory is an **independent git repository**. Always run git commands from within the target repo directory or use `-C`:

```bash
git -C kserve status
git -C odh-model-controller log --oneline -5
```

